The Probability refers to the 2D spatial probability of the
GW skymap enclosed in a given tile. The size of the tiles are 4.2x4.2 deg2
for TRE and 1.8 x 1.8 deg2 for TCA.
These observations cover 73% and 38% of the 90% GW probability skymap for
TRE and TCA respectively. The typical 3 sigma limiting magnitude for a
2 minute exposure is 17 for TRE and 18 for TCA. Results of the on-going
analysis  will be reported in a later GCNC.


GRANDMA (Global Rapid Advanced Network Devoted to the Multi-messenger
Addicts) is a network of robotic telescopes connected all over the
world with both photometry and spectrometry capabilities for Time-
domain Astronomy (https://grandma.lal.in2p3.fr/). Details on the TAROT
telescopes are available on the GRANDMA web pages or on
http://tarot.obs-hp.fr/

